  <span id="freeText15659222096037143244" style="display:none">Before there was Anne Rice... before there was Stephanie Meyer... there was Chelsea Quinn Yarbro and her Saint-Germain series. She is a grand master of horror. Read the entire series and you will marvel at the scope of her imagination. I can't praise her enough. I had a chance to meet her once at a Mystery Writers meeting out in San Francisco back in the 1970s. She was our guest speaker and displayed a wealth of knowledge that makes her books so enjoyable. To be brutally honest, no one comes close to her use of vampire lore and limitations.</span>
