<div id="review_2112263344" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2112263344" />
    <a title="Roger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5672633-roger"><img alt="Roger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1308710850p2/5672633.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2112263344?book_show_action=true">Sep 04, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roger" href="/user/show/5672633-roger">Roger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2112263344" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17963095007250490343">Hotel Transylvania features a non-sparkly vampire named St Germain. He has been a vampire so long he has forgotten when he became one. With a lifespan measured in the thousands of years, there are a lot of stories to tell about this character, and indeed there are now twenty seven books in the series. Hotel Transylvania is the first-it takes place in the 1790&apos;s and lets us learn a little about what type of vampire and person St Germain is. The writing is descriptive and baroque and a lot of fun </span>
  <span id="freeText17963095007250490343" style="display:none">Hotel Transylvania features a non-sparkly vampire named St Germain. He has been a vampire so long he has forgotten when he became one. With a lifespan measured in the thousands of years, there are a lot of stories to tell about this character, and indeed there are now twenty seven books in the series. Hotel Transylvania is the first-it takes place in the 1790's and lets us learn a little about what type of vampire and person St Germain is. The writing is descriptive and baroque and a lot of fun to read-it appears on the surface that Chelsea Quinn Yarbro has done her fair share of historical research. She spends a lot of time describing costuming, food etc. This really makes things interesting, and puts the reader squarely in the time period she is writing about. St. Germain is morally complicated-he is not the good guy so much as the slightly less bad guy. Good stuff.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17963095007250490343" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

