    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1672753618" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1672753618" />
    <a title="Timmy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/55189503-timmy"><img alt="Timmy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1461394545p2/55189503.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1672753618?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Timmy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Timmy" href="/user/show/55189503-timmy">Timmy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780312392482" href="/book/show/1062236.H_tel_Transylvania">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/55189503-timmy?shelf=gothic">gothic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/55189503-timmy?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/55189503-timmy?shelf=blacklace">blacklace</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1672753618" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11151049716188728278">In the historical fiction of Chelsea Quinn Yarbro, comes the first of her St. Germain vampire series, in all it&apos;s Gothic and well paced storytelling. It centers around the true-life mysterious Germain that actually lived, but Yarbro delves into a &quot;what-if&quot; tale of vampire fiction that has ample bite. Any fan of the coffin dwellers should welcome this work, and appreciate how well researched and written this book is, and understand that she has been copied by lesser authors since the publication </span>
  <span id="freeText11151049716188728278" style="display:none">In the historical fiction of Chelsea Quinn Yarbro, comes the first of her St. Germain vampire series, in all it's Gothic and well paced storytelling. It centers around the true-life mysterious Germain that actually lived, but Yarbro delves into a "what-if" tale of vampire fiction that has ample bite. Any fan of the coffin dwellers should welcome this work, and appreciate how well researched and written this book is, and understand that she has been copied by lesser authors since the publication of Hotel Transylvania in 1979. This meeting of Dark Shadows and The Scarlet Pimpernel, with a Satanic twist, should not be judged by, and compared to the sparkle-sparkle blood drinkers of the 2010s. If you allow your mind the chance to be swept into the cinematic grandeur of 1970's storytelling, such as Frank Langella's Dracula or Dan Curtis's Frankenstein, A True Story, then Hotel Transylvania will delight in bringing many a silent night to undead life. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11151049716188728278" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

